Location: New York > The Gunks > The Trapps > a1. The Uberfall - left

Notes: Easy climbing lots of small gear than into roof crux protect with .4 directly above head pull the roof than move onto anchors ledge. Lots of fun Louis led second pitch just as fun but easier some roofy moves. After finishing climb there is a sketchy left traverse to ribs repel.
Location: New York > The Gunks > The Trapps > d. Strictly - The Ceiling

Notes: Took at the first crux got pumped out on the layback. Thin finger cracks and interesting movement shifting body weight left and right. Second pitch lots of fun placed micro two to protect under roof than into traverse following corner up.
Location: New York > The Gunks > The Trapps > e. The Mac Wall (Something Interesting)

Notes: Lots of confusion. Connected first and second pitch which lead to lots of rope drag. Would probably never do this way again. The chimney was interesting and felt tricky. Misread the Topo and thought I made it to the anchors after the diagonal crack. I was very wrong. Lots of loose poor quality rock. Ended up on variation 1? Forgot to clip my rope to protection I placed above ledge with trees, ended up running out thirty or so feet. Oops. Only redeemable quality of this climb was variation 1 finishes with a nice corner crack for about 10-15 feet. Would never do this variation again because of rope drag. Looking forward to trying to pull the ceiling on a later date.
Location: New York > The Gunks > The Trapps > d. Strictly - The Ceiling

Notes: Quick warm up. Showed Katya repelling techniques. Dropped phone when starting repel. Phone was okay! Breezed through crack just shove your whole body in and it’s a breeze!
Location: New York > The Gunks > The Trapps > c. Frog's Head - the Arch

Notes: Beautiful climb lots of fun. First pitch is a breeze. 2nd pitch has a spicy over hang to a drawn out slab with a big left move finish on small well protected crimps!
